      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 1967: reloadBodyOverwriteMessages only erases the exact key bodyOverwrite, but the comment says it clears bodyOverwrite* entries. If plugins use related cached keys, stale data can survive a reload and be mixed with regenerated overwrites. Either fix the comment or clear by prefix consistently. Suggested implementation:\n```suggestion\nfor (auto it \u003d msg-\u003epluginData.begin(); it !\u003d msg-\u003epluginData.end();) {\n    if (it-\u003efirst.rfind(\"bodyOverwrite\", 0) \u003d\u003d 0)\n        it \u003d msg-\u003epluginData.erase(it);\n    else\n        ++it;\n}\n```",
