      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 2035: loadMissingBodyOverwrites treats an absent bodyOverwrite as work still pending, but when the plugin returns no overwrite the message is left absent. This means every subsequent load retriggers plugin transformation for the same messages/editions, which can become very expensive for large conversations or translation plugins. Store an explicit processed/empty state or restrict this to plugin preference changes. For example:\n```suggestion\nif (boIt !\u003d single[0].pluginData.end()) {\n    std::lock_guard writeLk(loadedHistory_.mutex);\n    auto realIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(work.id);\n    if (realIt !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end())\n        realIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d boIt-\u003esecond;\n    anySyncSet \u003d !boIt-\u003esecond.empty();\n} else {\n    std::lock_guard writeLk(loadedHistory_.mutex);\n    auto realIt \u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.find(work.id);\n    if (realIt !\u003d loadedHistory_.quickAccess.end())\n        realIt-\u003esecond-\u003epluginData[\"bodyOverwrite\"] \u003d \"\";\n}\n```",
